===Etymology 1===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|lien|lang=enm}}, {{term|liggen|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|licgan|lang=ang}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{recons|ligjaną|lang=gem-pro}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{recons|legʰ-|lang=ine-pro}}. Cognate with West Frisian {{term|lizze|lang=fy}}, Dutch {{term|liggen|lang=en}}, German {{term|liegen|lang=en}}, Danish {{term|ligge|lang=en}}, Swedish {{term|ligga|lang=en}}, Gothic {{term|𐌻𐌹𐌲𐌰𐌽|tr=ligan|lang=got}}; and with Latin {{term|lectus||bed|lang=la}}, Irish {{term|luighe|lang=en}}, Russian {{term|лежать|lang=ru}}, Albanian {{term|lagje||inhabited area, neighbourhood|lang=sq}}.

As a noun for {{term|position|lang=en}}, the [[#Noun|noun]] has the same etymology above as the [[#Verb|verb]].

